article.headline: Stetson 58, Savannah State 46
article.story: SAVANNAH, Ga. (AP) -- Garfield Blair scored 16 points and keyed a decisive 14-4 run that powered Stetson to a 58-46 victory over Savannah State on Saturday. Gabe McMillen scored 17 points and Tim Lang blocked four shots to help Stetson (4-8) to its first road win of the season. It was only the second home loss of the season for Savannah State (6-11). Lazarius Coleman scored 12 points for Savannah State. Stetson trailed by five points early in the second half, but a three-point play by Blair pulled the Hatters into a tie before McMillen hit a jump shot to put Stetson ahead for good.
